Description: Fragment of a faience ring bezel, very flat, poor quality faience, the ring itself is not preserved. The upper part of the ring bezel shows hieroglyphs: j-p:t-H on top of a nb-basket, surrounded by a circumferential line. Original colour might have been light green.
Bibliographic references: Spencer 1997 / Amara West I, The Architectural Report (p. 182)
